1
00:00:02,628 --> 00:00:05,631
[footsteps]

2
00:00:15,015 --> 00:00:16,516
What is it? [grunts]

3
00:00:16,517 --> 00:00:18,476
Diana Taverner is downstairs.

4
00:00:18,477 --> 00:00:22,689
[sighs] Tell her I'll be down
in five minutes.

5
00:00:22,773 --> 00:00:25,651
Um, she says to come straight down.

6
00:00:26,860 --> 00:00:29,571
- [Olivia] What's going on, darling?
- Nothing, darling. [kisses]

7
00:00:58,392 --> 00:01:00,143
[River]
I wonder what the others are up to.

8
00:01:04,397 --> 00:01:07,277
Could have called them if you hadn't
thrown away Min and Louisa's phones.

9
00:01:09,194 --> 00:01:16,201
Should let them know
they're not being hunted anymore, in case they're halfway through some dodgy backstreet plastic surgery.

10
00:01:16,869 --> 00:01:18,245
[snores]

11
00:01:21,832 --> 00:01:23,876
[snoring]

12
00:01:25,210 --> 00:01:28,213
["Strange Game" playing]

13
00:02:14,510 --> 00:02:16,094
Can't hack the satnav.

14
00:02:16,178 --> 00:02:19,139
- [Min] Because?
- Cheap bastards didn't hire one.

15
00:02:19,223 --> 00:02:21,307
Or the flash bastards had their own.

16
00:02:21,308 --> 00:02:28,481
What I have done,
and which is beneath you puny mortals, is hack into the van's Theft Recovery Transmitter.

17
00:02:28,482 --> 00:02:29,858
So we can track it?

18
00:02:30,484 --> 00:02:34,071
Signal's intermittent,
so you'll only get where the vehicle is or was every ten minutes.

19
00:02:34,821 --> 00:02:36,281
But they're heading east on the A12.

20
00:02:36,365 --> 00:02:39,618
Last ping from a petrol station
just outside Chelmsford.

21
00:02:40,244 --> 00:02:42,829
- What? So what do we do with this?
- Well, we call it in.

22
00:02:42,913 --> 00:02:45,749
To the Park? When they're trying to hang
the kidnap on us?

23
00:02:46,583 --> 00:02:48,085
Then we get it to someone else.

24
00:02:58,178 --> 00:02:59,179
[door closes]

25
00:02:59,263 --> 00:03:04,142
[Peter]
Diana. I'm afraid our maid is asleep, so it's me on char duty. What can I get you?

26
00:03:04,226 --> 00:03:06,895
Tea, please. Assam if you have it,
builder's otherwise.

27
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:08,438
Milk, no sugar.

28
00:03:08,981 --> 00:03:11,733
- So, you know why I'm here?
- [Peter] I've no idea why you're here.

29
00:03:11,817 --> 00:03:13,735
I think you do.
Otherwise, you'd have asked.

30
00:03:13,819 --> 00:03:17,489
I've a woman in my kitchen I've met
a few times on the cocktail party circuit.

31
00:03:17,573 --> 00:03:20,742
I'm more concerned with how I'm going
to explain your presence to my wife.

32
00:03:20,826 --> 00:03:22,702
I can give her a précis if you like.

33
00:03:22,703 --> 00:03:27,291
We know from phone records
that Robert Hobden called you yesterday afternoon, repeatedly.

34
00:03:27,791 --> 00:03:32,295
None of the calls lasted
more than 15 seconds so clearly he couldn't get through.

35
00:03:32,296 --> 00:03:42,389
Now, I could pull CCTV
from surrounding streets to confirm what I already know but don't have the time to prove, which is that Hobden eventually turned up here, desperate to talk to you.

36
00:03:44,349 --> 00:03:46,309
Oh, would you believe it?
After all that, no Assam.

37
00:03:46,310 --> 00:03:47,394
Have to be builder's.

38
00:03:47,978 --> 00:03:50,939
By the way, um,
what's his name, hmm, Hobden?

39
00:03:51,481 --> 00:03:52,690
Haven't seen him for years.

40
00:03:52,691 --> 00:03:54,359
Doubt I'd recognize him if I did.

41
00:03:54,443 --> 00:04:07,956
Another thing I know but don't have
the time to prove at this exact moment is that after Hobden's visit, calls were made, by you or someone close to you, to certain individuals with links to the people who kidnapped Hassan Ahmed.

42
00:04:08,957 --> 00:04:15,004
Again, I could pull up the phone records
for everyone in this building, starting with the man listening at the door.

43
00:04:15,005 --> 00:04:17,257
[footsteps departing]

44
00:04:17,341 --> 00:04:19,134
And, of course, your phone records.

45
00:04:19,218 --> 00:04:22,846
I'm guessing there might be some numbers
you don't want your wife to know about.

46
00:04:23,347 --> 00:04:27,017
Those to the mothers of the children
she's not aware of, perhaps?

47
00:04:28,352 --> 00:04:31,354
- I have a very open marriage.
- I don't give a fuck about your marriage!

48
00:04:31,355 --> 00:04:37,861
I have a dead agent at the scene of a
kidnapping and a boy who's God knows where who'll be next to die, all because of a phone call you made.

49
00:04:37,945 --> 00:04:40,948
I wish I could help you, Diana,
but I made no such call.

50
00:04:43,492 --> 00:04:46,411
I'm gonna turn on the kettle
for the tea you've failed to make.

51
00:04:46,495 --> 00:04:53,085
If you're not talking straight with me
by the time it boils, I'm going to call in the Dogs and begin the process of turning your life inside out.

52
00:04:55,629 --> 00:04:56,755
Okay, thank you.

53
00:05:10,644 --> 00:05:15,815
Judging by the tone of the woman
who answered the phone, this was likely the 1,000th tip they received today.

54
00:05:15,816 --> 00:05:17,817
Well, surely it made
a difference coming from you.

55
00:05:17,818 --> 00:05:19,486
Well, who was I to say was calling?

56
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:21,068
"Oh, hello, Scotland Yard?

57
00:05:21,113 --> 00:05:27,870
I'm with the punishment detail at MI5,
although at present, they're hunting me for the kidnapping that I'm trying to help you solve."

58
00:05:29,246 --> 00:05:30,247
[sighs]

59
00:05:37,004 --> 00:05:38,129
I'm going.

60
00:05:38,130 --> 00:05:40,256
- Where?
- Down the A12.

61
00:05:40,257 --> 00:05:42,926
- You'll never catch them.
- I might if I put my foot down.

62
00:05:43,010 --> 00:05:44,469
Pigs'll pull you over for speeding.

63
00:05:44,553 --> 00:05:45,720
How many times, we're the pigs.

64
00:05:45,721 --> 00:05:47,407
I won't stop.
I'll lead them to the kidnappers.

65
00:05:47,431 --> 00:05:49,111
[Louisa] Hey. Hold on. I'll come with you.

66
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:52,769
Roddy and I will go to Lamb's flat,
in case he shows.

67
00:05:52,853 --> 00:05:54,187
[Roddy] Lamb's not at his flat.

68
00:05:54,188 --> 00:05:55,522
And how do you know that?

69
00:05:55,606 --> 00:05:59,151
I put a tracker on his car a year ago.
I put one on all of your cars.

70
00:06:01,778 --> 00:06:05,324
What? I did it precisely
for a situation like this.

71
00:06:10,704 --> 00:06:12,247
[kettle boiling]

72
00:06:16,543 --> 00:06:20,171
This isn't about whether or not
Hobden was here or if I made a call.

73
00:06:20,172 --> 00:06:23,925
You're on the clock
and need me to do something, so why don't you just come out and ask?

74
00:06:23,926 --> 00:06:28,179
I want you to use your contacts in the far right to connect with the head of the Sons of Albion.

75
00:06:28,180 --> 00:06:31,141
Find out where his boys might go
if they wanted to leave the country.

76
00:06:31,225 --> 00:06:32,559
I don't know Simmonds.

77
00:06:32,643 --> 00:06:34,394
You went grouse shooting
with him last year.

78
00:06:34,478 --> 00:06:36,229
There were a lot of people on that shoot.

79
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:38,815
Just the two of you golfing
at Sunningdale, though.

80
00:06:38,899 --> 00:06:42,486
My sources say he thrashed you,
which is probably why you blanked it.

81
00:06:42,986 --> 00:06:44,362
Why should he do me any favors?

82
00:06:44,363 --> 00:06:48,283
Tell him I don't have time
to kick his door in, but I will if he leaves me no option.

83
00:06:48,367 --> 00:06:52,496
He gives them up within five minutes, or the pair of you are having breakfast in a holding cell.

84
00:06:53,539 --> 00:06:55,915
I know about the Frontline Club, Diana.

85
00:06:55,916 --> 00:06:59,878
And what Hobden overheard you say
to your brother, was it?

86
00:06:59,962 --> 00:07:03,590
Your one card. Are you sure
you want to play that now?

87
00:07:03,674 --> 00:07:06,176
Now is the only time to play it.
Game'll be over soon.

88
00:07:06,260 --> 00:07:07,761
Then go and get dressed.

89
00:07:08,887 --> 00:07:11,598
I'll take the hit when it comes,
but you are going to the Park.

90
00:07:11,682 --> 00:07:15,185
Down to a floor with no number.
I'd wear something comfortable.

91
00:07:15,269 --> 00:07:18,062
Something you don't mind ruining
with piss, shit and blood.

92
00:07:18,063 --> 00:07:21,316
Now, now, Diana, I'm not suggesting
mutually assured destruction.

93
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,651
What are you suggesting?

94
00:07:23,318 --> 00:07:24,778
You and I share the same problem.

95
00:07:26,154 --> 00:07:28,657
Connection to the unsavories
through one man.

96
00:07:29,283 --> 00:07:30,325
Robert Hobden.

97
00:07:33,996 --> 00:07:36,707
I hope you don't mind if I listen in
when you make your calls.

98
00:08:00,063 --> 00:08:02,024
How the fuck did you find us?

99
00:08:06,278 --> 00:08:09,030
Oh, well, put it back.
It'll come in handy if it gets nicked.

100
00:08:09,031 --> 00:08:12,742
They haven't cuffed us.
You must have the photographs.

101
00:08:12,743 --> 00:08:16,079
- Yeah. We checkmated Taverner.
- Were you planning on telling us?

102
00:08:16,163 --> 00:08:18,289
No, I was enjoying not seeing you.

103
00:08:18,290 --> 00:08:19,541
Where are Min and Louisa?

104
00:08:19,625 --> 00:08:22,168
Well, Ho worked out a way
to track the kidnappers.

105
00:08:22,169 --> 00:08:24,045
Min and Louisa are chasing after them.

106
00:08:24,046 --> 00:08:27,799
My orders were pretty clear. Do fuck all!

107
00:08:27,883 --> 00:08:32,304
You've let two Slow Horses tear off
in a doomed attempt to try and not make things worse.

108
00:08:32,386 --> 00:08:35,015
I didn't let them.
Jackson, they're autonomous beings.

109
00:08:35,097 --> 00:08:38,559
I just hope they only get themselves
killed and don't set an orphanage on fire.

110
00:08:39,394 --> 00:08:43,064
[grunts] Keep tracking that van.
Let me know if it so much as changes lane.

111
00:08:43,065 --> 00:08:44,149
[door opens]

112
00:08:45,192 --> 00:08:46,712
[Catherine] Think they're headed here.

113
00:08:46,777 --> 00:08:48,153
[car engine starts]

114
00:08:48,237 --> 00:08:50,989
This is Duffy.
Get a tactical team airborne. Now.

115
00:08:53,784 --> 00:08:55,201
[Jackson] They're headed to Harwich.

116
00:08:55,202 --> 00:08:56,536
How did you know?

117
00:08:56,537 --> 00:09:01,750
Black used an old legend to hire a van.
Ho accessed the van's theft locator.

118
00:09:01,834 --> 00:09:05,211
They're on the, uh, A12.
Nearest port is Harwich.

119
00:09:05,212 --> 00:09:09,216
Standish and Ho will give you
all the various. I'm off for a kip.

120
00:09:14,471 --> 00:09:16,682
You're not actually
gonna go to bed, are you?

121
00:09:17,891 --> 00:09:19,226
You have something for us?

122
00:09:20,352 --> 00:09:23,021
That's the van's plate number
and the ID for the theft locator.

123
00:09:23,105 --> 00:09:25,064
[Diana] They're going after
the kidnappers, aren't they?

124
00:09:25,065 --> 00:09:26,983
God, men are such boys.

125
00:09:26,984 --> 00:09:32,489
Uh, ma'am, while I appreciate you
offering to include me in your circle of sisterhood, I'll have to decline.

126
00:09:33,156 --> 00:09:37,410
Unless you want to fulfill
the promise you made and tell me what you know about Partner's death?

127
00:09:37,411 --> 00:09:41,206
That ship sailed, Standish,
when you pulled a gun on one of my Dogs.

128
00:09:41,290 --> 00:09:45,919
Just think, if you'd returned my call,
you'd be back at the Park tomorrow.

129
00:09:46,003 --> 00:09:48,005
And why on earth would I want that?

130
00:09:49,882 --> 00:09:51,049
- Roddy.
- What?

131
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:53,510
- Shut up and keep walking.
- Where?

132
00:09:53,594 --> 00:09:55,095
- Slough House.
- No, but that's...

133
00:09:55,179 --> 00:09:58,473
I know it's the other way, Roddy,
but I was in dire need of a dramatic exit.

134
00:09:59,016 --> 00:10:01,351
Do not look back.
That's just what she wants.

135
00:10:19,536 --> 00:10:21,621
They stopped for petrol,
headed east 20 minutes ago.

136
00:10:21,622 --> 00:10:23,600
- Sure it was them?
- Yeah, they made Hassan get it.

137
00:10:23,624 --> 00:10:24,791
Hassan? Why make him...

138
00:10:24,875 --> 00:10:26,918
The guy remembered him
because he left a tip.

139
00:10:26,919 --> 00:10:28,461
Did you not get any food?

140
00:10:28,462 --> 00:10:30,088
You can see I didn't. Let's go, Min.

141
00:10:30,172 --> 00:10:31,881
Do you mind if I nip in and get something?

142
00:10:31,882 --> 00:10:36,386
Yeah, sure. Only if you don't mind
admitting at Hassan's inquest that we arrived late because you needed crisps.

143
00:10:36,470 --> 00:10:37,471
Okay, okay.

144
00:10:39,681 --> 00:10:41,099
Jesus Christ, Min. Hurry up!

145
00:10:41,183 --> 00:10:45,145
All right! I just function better
on a bit of food, that's all.

146
00:10:45,229 --> 00:10:46,396
Oh, for God's sake.

147
00:10:57,658 --> 00:10:59,284
[Curly] I was seven, maybe eight.

148
00:10:59,368 --> 00:11:02,662
It was the first castle I saw up close.
All in ruins.

149
00:11:02,663 --> 00:11:07,918
You could play around it, climb on it.
My granddad said it was Norman.

150
00:11:09,002 --> 00:11:10,337
Very old. [sighs]

151
00:11:11,839 --> 00:11:13,257
As England as England could be.

152
00:11:16,176 --> 00:11:17,385
Be a good spot for it.

153
00:11:17,386 --> 00:11:20,889
- [Larry] Can we just go to the boat?
- How's your memory?

154
00:11:21,390 --> 00:11:22,390
Fine. What?

155
00:11:22,391 --> 00:11:26,853
'Cause you seem to be forgetting
what happened to the last person who asked, "Can we not just go to the boat?"

156
00:11:26,854 --> 00:11:29,814
Whoa, whoa, no, I mean... I mean
we'll kill him, yeah? We'll kill him!

157
00:11:29,815 --> 00:11:33,109
All right? But... [stammers]
at the harbor or the boat or something...

158
00:11:33,110 --> 00:11:34,194
Are you sure about that?

159
00:11:34,278 --> 00:11:37,655
Because it's pretty tricky swinging an axe
on a boat. I might miss. I might hit you.

160
00:11:37,656 --> 00:11:40,617
- Mate, time is running out...
- So is my fucking patience!

161
00:11:40,701 --> 00:11:41,993
Fucking hell!

162
00:11:41,994 --> 00:11:44,913
He won't shoot you at the wheel.
We'd crash, w-we might all die.

163
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:50,043
Well, you're not at the wheel, are you?
What's to stop me shooting you?

164
00:11:51,211 --> 00:11:53,172
Because you want to chop my head off.

165
00:11:53,881 --> 00:11:55,632
You want me on my knees, remember?

166
00:11:57,676 --> 00:11:58,760
Not long now.

167
00:12:04,558 --> 00:12:05,998
[Roddy] Van's 20 miles ahead of you.

168
00:12:06,727 --> 00:12:07,936
Min and Louisa?

169
00:12:08,562 --> 00:12:09,604
Ten miles.

170
00:12:09,605 --> 00:12:11,481
Are you into the Park's feed?

171
00:12:12,065 --> 00:12:13,733
[sighs] Was nearly there when you called.

172
00:12:13,734 --> 00:12:16,569
- Then stop talking!
- Well, no, no, wait, wait, wait, Roddy.

173
00:12:16,570 --> 00:12:20,657
When you get a sec,
can you get into the hospital's system and find out how Sid is? And...

174
00:12:22,284 --> 00:12:23,284
What the fuck?

175
00:12:23,285 --> 00:12:24,578
[line beeping]

176
00:12:25,329 --> 00:12:29,499
You need to hear this from me,
not an insensitive prick like him.

177
00:12:32,294 --> 00:12:33,337
What, she's gone?

178
00:12:36,840 --> 00:12:37,841
Yeah.

179
00:12:43,388 --> 00:12:44,515
[exhales deeply]

180
00:12:47,601 --> 00:12:48,852
Count yourself lucky.

181
00:12:50,145 --> 00:12:51,271
Jesus Chri...

182
00:12:52,397 --> 00:12:54,691
Yeah, lucky me. Yeah.

183
00:12:54,775 --> 00:12:58,195
From my end of the telescope,
surviving's the short straw.

184
00:13:02,157 --> 00:13:07,037
By the time I was your age,
I'd lost a baker's dozen.

185
00:13:10,332 --> 00:13:15,087
It was bad enough when the Wall was up, but once they reduced it to bricks and rubble, everything went to shit.

186
00:13:16,213 --> 00:13:19,716
Whole networks of joes rounded up, blown.

187
00:13:21,301 --> 00:13:22,803
I haven't forgotten any of them.

188
00:13:26,139 --> 00:13:27,558
And I won't forget Sid.

189
00:13:32,521 --> 00:13:36,983
- Besides, she was the only one of you...
- Who wasn't complete shit.

190
00:13:36,984 --> 00:13:38,777
Yeah, yeah. You... You've said that.

191
00:13:40,404 --> 00:13:47,244
- [clears throat]
- [sniffles] Any rate, the moral of the story is, get used to death.

192
00:13:49,329 --> 00:13:51,372
Cause you're gonna see a lot more of it.

193
00:13:51,373 --> 00:13:54,501
And if that scares you,
then open the door and roll out now.

194
00:14:20,027 --> 00:14:22,112
Out. Get the f...

195
00:14:25,532 --> 00:14:26,658
[Curly] Get our friend out.

196
00:14:32,039 --> 00:14:33,456
- [gasps]
- [Curly] Get rid of him.

197
00:14:33,457 --> 00:14:35,292
In there. And you're helping.

198
00:14:35,876 --> 00:14:37,044
You get his legs. Go on.

199
00:14:40,339 --> 00:14:42,049
[both grunting]

200
00:14:58,398 --> 00:15:01,527
Once he's killed me, he's gonna
wanna go out in a blaze of glory.

201
00:15:03,111 --> 00:15:06,049
If you're with him, - you'll get killed in the cross fire. - Shut up!

202
00:15:06,073 --> 00:15:09,243
All right. Tie his hands and feet.
Make sure he can't run.

203
00:15:13,664 --> 00:15:16,666
- Help me escape. Please. [grunts]
- Shut the fuck up!

204
00:15:16,667 --> 00:15:18,210
[Curly] The fuck's going on in there?

205
00:15:20,629 --> 00:15:23,339
You didn't know. You didn't know.
[breathes heavily]

206
00:15:23,340 --> 00:15:25,759
[car doors slam]

207
00:15:30,138 --> 00:15:32,140
All right, get up. Here.

208
00:15:33,267 --> 00:15:35,811
Fucking... Go on. Go on.

209
00:15:51,827 --> 00:15:53,412
[engine spluttering]

210
00:15:59,459 --> 00:16:00,960
[Louisa] What the hell, Min?

211
00:16:00,961 --> 00:16:02,546
I've run out of petrol.

212
00:16:03,297 --> 00:16:04,798
[Louisa] Are you fucking kidding?

213
00:16:05,465 --> 00:16:08,176
How can we be out of petrol?
We were just at a petrol station.

214
00:16:08,177 --> 00:16:10,530
[Min] Well, hang on. We were...
We weren't stopping for petrol.

215
00:16:10,554 --> 00:16:12,532
Yeah, I know.
Otherwise you'd have got fucking petrol!

216
00:16:12,556 --> 00:16:13,640
We were stopping for intel.

217
00:16:13,724 --> 00:16:16,602
I got the intel! What were you doing
whilst I was doing that?

218
00:16:17,477 --> 00:16:19,521
I... I was distracted.
I was thinking about stuff.

219
00:16:19,605 --> 00:16:20,688
[Louisa] What stuff? Huh?

220
00:16:20,689 --> 00:16:22,273
I don't know. Nothing. [stammers]

221
00:16:22,274 --> 00:16:26,027
No, no one thinks about nothing, Min, unless they're a Zen master. Are you a Zen master?

222
00:16:26,028 --> 00:16:28,738
No, I'm not! No, I'm tired. I'm...
I was thinking about sleeping.

223
00:16:28,739 --> 00:16:29,823
Food, you know.

224
00:16:30,324 --> 00:16:32,117
- Fuck.
- Oh, my God.

225
